question: You are given a string num representing a large integer. An integer is good if it meets the following conditions:

It is a substring of num with length 3.
It consists of only one unique digit.
Return the maximum good integer as a string or an empty string "" if no such integer exists.

Note:

A substring is a contiguous sequence of characters within a string.
There may be leading zeroes in num or a good integer.

code:

class Solution {
public:
    // Function to find the largest good integer in the given string
    string largestGoodInteger(string num) {
        string best = ""; // Initialize an empty string to hold the best (largest) good integer
        
        // Iterate through the string, checking for groups of three identical digits
        for (int i = 0; i + 2 < num.size(); i++) {
            // Check if the current digit and the next two digits are the same
            if (num[i] == num[i + 1] && num[i] == num[i + 2]) {
                // If they are the same, extract the substring of the three digits
                // and compare it with the current best
                best = max(best, num.substr(i, 3));
            }
        }
        
        // Return the largest good integer found, or an empty string if none were found
        return best;
    }
};
